20radical%20they%20are.%20And%20that%20depends%20on%20where%20Congress%20is.%20If%20they%20have%20a%20Democratic%20Congress%2C%20they%20won't%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20do%20what%20they%20would%20do%20with%20a%20Republican%20Congress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStiglitz%20recently%20spearheaded%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24777566-nobel-letter-final%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20signed%20by%20over%20a%20dozen%20Nobel%20Prize-winning%20economists.%20The%20letter%2C%20which%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2024%2F06%2F25%2Fnobel-prize-winners-biden-economy-trump-inflation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20obtained%20by%20Axios%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stated%20the%20economists%20were%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20risks%20of%20a%20second%20Trump%20administration%20for%20the%20U.S.%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economists%20predicted%20dire%20results%20from%20a%20Trump%20victory%20this%20fall.%20%26quot%3BThe%20outcome%20of%20this%20election%20will%20have%20economic%20repercussions%20for%20years%2C%20and%20possibly%20decades%2C%20to%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20stated.%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20a%20second%20Trump%20term%20would%20have%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20the%20U.S.'s%20economic%20standing%20in%20the%20world%20and%20a%20destabilizing%20effect%20on%20the%20U.S.'s%20domestic%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Trump%20had%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-watch-presidential-debate-trump-biden-what-time-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20presidential%20debate%20of%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday.%20There%20are%20still%20a%20little%20over%20four%20months%20until%20the%20election%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.fivethirtyeight.com%2F2024-election-forecast%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFiveThirtyEight%3C%2Fa%3E%20reports%20as%20of%20June%2025%20its%20forecast%20finds%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bpure%20toss-up%26quot%3B%20who%20will%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20talked%20to%20Stiglitz%20about%20the%20economy%20if%20Trump%20is%20once%20again%20president.%20Stiglitz%20said%20the%20widely%20shared%20view%20is%20this%20could%20result%20in%20higher%20inflation%2C%20worse%20inequality%2C%20and%20a%20potential%20broader%20economic%20slowdown.%20Massive%20progress%20has%20already%20been%20made%20in%20cooling%20off%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FiBARz%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Consumer%20price%20index%20inflation%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22443%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EStiglitz%20pointed%20out%20how%20remarkably%20the%20inflation%20rate%20had%20cooled%20down%20without%20leading%20to%20high%20unemployment.%20The%20US%20unemployment%20rate%20has%20been%20at%20or%20under%204%25%20since%20the%20end%20of%202021%2C%20a%20historically%20long%20stretch%20of%20low%20joblessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStiglitz%20noted%20Trump's%20promise%20of%20large%20increases%20in%20tariffs%20as%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20could%20make%20inflation%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20tariffs%20overwhelmingly%20get%20passed%20on%20to%20consumers%20and%20increasing%20their%20prices%20and%20get%20fed%20down%20the%20supply%20chain%20%E2%80%94%20again%2C%20increasing%20prices%20to%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20Stiglitz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20could%20be%20the%20large%20decrease%20in%20taxes%20Trump%20proposed%20%26quot%3Bthat%20are%20not%20paid%20for%20and%20increasing%20the%20budgetary%20deficit%20from%20the%20level%20that%20it%20is%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Stiglitz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20given%20where%20we%20are%2C%20I%20think%20the%20broad%20assessment%20is%20that%20that%20would%20be%20inflationary%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20broad%20assessment%20of%20the%20consequences%20of%20that%20is%20that%20the%20Fed%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20raise%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20all%20that%20combined%20would%20still%20serve%20to%20increase%20inflation%20even%20as%20unemployment%20increased%20and%20GDP%20slowed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20third%20factor%20that%20could%20juice%20inflation%20would%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bdrastic%20reductions%20in%20immigration%26quot%3B%20that%20Trump%20has%20proposed%2C%20Stiglitz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20different%20sectors%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20that%20rely%20on%20immigration%2C%20and%20Stiglitz%20said%20that%20the%20tight%20labor%20market%20could%20become%20even%20tighter%20with%20this%20drop%20in%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStiglitz%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epossibility%20of%20a%20partial%20or%20full%20repeal%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-heres-whats-in-the-manchin-deal-for-bidens-agenda-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInflation%20Reduction%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20included%20a%20Medicare%20prescription%20drug%20provision%2C%20among%20other%20things.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20that%2C%20which%20Republicans%20had%20talked%20about%20repealing%2C%20drug%20prices%20will%20go%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20the%20risks%20to%20inflation%2C%20Stiglitz%20said%20a%20Trump%20presidency%20could%20also%20mean%20a%20slowing%20GDP.%20Another%20problem%20that%20could%20get%20worse%20is%20the%20inequality%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStiglitz%20pointed%20to%20Trump's%20tax%20policy%20as%20one%20that%20could%20boost%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20tax%20cut%20is%20a%20tax%20cut%20for%20the%20corporations%20and%20the%20billionaires%2C%26quot%3B%20Stiglitz%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20share%20of%20the%20tax%20cuts%20that%20go%20to%20the%20bottom%2C%20very%20small.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20some%20of%20my%20analysis%20I%20suggested%20that%20it's%20even%20possible%20that%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20bottom%20would%20see%20a%20tax%20increase.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F06%2F26%2Fbusiness%2Fnobel-economists-trump-inflation%2Findex.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DInflation%2520remains%2520public%2520enemy%2520No%2Cthey%2520would%2520make%2520matters%2520worse.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Ftrump-economy-nobel-prize-winners-letter-inflation-warning%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eothers%3C%2Fa%3E%20noted%20statements%20from%20the%20Trump%20campaign%20disagreeing%20with%20the%20letter%20that%20the%2016%20economists%20signed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20American%20people%20don't%20need%20worthless%20out%20of%20touch%20Nobel%20prize%20winners%20to%20tell%20them%20which%20president%20put%20more%20money%20in%20their%20pockets%2C%26quot%3B%20Karoline%20Leavitt%2C%20the%20Trump%20campaign's%20national%20press%20secretary%2C%20told%20CNN%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BAmericans%20know%20we%20cannot%20afford%20four%20more%20years%20of%20Bidenomics%2C%20and%20when%20President%20Trump%20is%20back%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20he%20will%20reimplement%20his%20pro-growth%2C%20pro-energy%2C%20pro-jobs%20agenda%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20uplift%20all%20Americans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-presidency-policies-inflation-economy-americans-joseph-stiglitz-letter-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719568382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667d992440cf2af6e4f64d9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessins