ame%20a%20mechanic%20instead.%20I%20ended%20up%20getting%20a%20dream%20job%20at%20Tesla.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222208%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Diana%20Welsch%20working%20on%20a%20Tesla%20car%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6671aa87087acd2be9b48d70%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221656%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDiana%20Welsch%20worked%20as%20a%20mobile%20technician%20for%20Tesla%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20which%20she%20called%20a%20'dream%20job.'%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Diana%20Welsch%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDiana%20Welsch%20went%20to%20art%20school%20before%20deciding%20to%20train%20as%20a%20car%20mechanic%20at%2025.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20she%20landed%20a%20job%20as%20a%20trainee%20at%20Tesla%2C%20she%20moved%20from%20Arizona%20to%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20it%20was%20the%20best%20job%20she%20ever%20had%2C%20but%20she%20left%20in%202023%20because%20of%20the%20pressure%20at%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Diana%20Welsch%20about%20training%20to%20be%20a%20car%20mechanic%20instead%20of%20going%20to%20grad%20school.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20income%20and%20employment.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20admired%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectrician-switched-medicine-surgeon-degree-college-pre-med-gen-z-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20who%20can%20fix%20things%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20brought%20up%20in%20an%20upper-middle-class%20area%20in%20Arizona%2C%20where%20going%20into%20a%20trade%20was%20generally%20not%20seen%20as%20a%20viable%20option.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-collar-job-demand-growth-white-collar-layoffs-ai-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlue-collar%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20looked%20down%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20age%20of%2017%2C%20I%20worked%20part-time%20in%20a%20library%20in%20Phoenix.%20After%20graduating%20from%20high%20school%20in%202003%2C%20I%20went%20to%20college%20and%20studied%20art.%20I%20kept%20up%20my%20library%20job%20on%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20needed%20a%20proper%20job%20after%20college.%20You%20had%20to%20go%20to%20grad%20school%20to%20become%20a%20librarian%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20car%20kept%20breaking%20down%2C%20and%20my%20friend%20would%20help%20me%20fix%20it.%20I%20loved%20working%20under%20the%20hood%20of%20a%20car%20and%20realized%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20mechanic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22942ca134-0605-4145-a2b0-40ebf592203f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20went%20to%20trade%20school%20instead%20of%20grad%20school%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20trade%20school%20in%202014.%20My%20mom%2C%20who%20had%20left%20blue-collar%20work%20for%20a%20white-collar%20job%2C%20didn't%20understand%20my%20decision.%20I%20took%20out%20a%20student%20loan%20and%20enrolled%20at%20Universal%20Technical%20Institute%20in%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20one-year%20program%2C%20I%20started%20working%20in%20garages.%20At%20various%20points%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20Chevy%2C%20Meineke%2C%20and%20Sun%20Devil%20Auto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20the%20way%2C%20I%20encountered%20various%20obstacles.%20For%20one%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20wasn't%20being%20taken%20seriously%2C%20and%20it%20seemed%20like%20it%20was%20because%20I%20was%20a%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff49cfa4-00c1-49d8-a9c0-ecdd9fa1f601%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20got%20a%20dream%20job%20at%20Tesla%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20my%20trade%20school%20fair%2C%20I%20saw%20that%20Tesla%20was%20hiring%20trainees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20and%20got%20the%20Tesla%20traineeship%20in%202017%2C%20which%20was%20based%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20It%20was%20a%20dream%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20was%20different%20from%20my%20other%20jobs.%20From%20day%20one%2C%20they%20took%20me%20seriously%20and%20gave%20me%20real%20work.%20They%20paired%20me%20with%20an%20experienced%20technician.%20After%20a%20few%20months%2C%20I%20could%20do%20repairs%20at%20the%20level%20my%20mentor%20had%20been%20working%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20years%2C%20I%20was%20transferred%20to%20their%20mobile%20service%20department.%20My%20job%20was%20to%20drive%20to%20people's%20houses%20and%20workplaces%20in%20my%20Tesla%20Model%20S%20to%20repair%20their%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20do%20basic%20repairs%2C%20such%20as%20replacing%20windscreen%20wipers%2C%20batteries%2C%20or%20air%20filters%20or%20fixing%20their%20window%20or%20door%20if%20it%20stopped%20opening.%20I'd%20also%20help%20with%20customer%20education%20%E2%80%94%20when%20people%20need%20help%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20use%20a%20feature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Tesla's%20clientele%20were%20older%20and%20affluent.%20Sometimes%2C%20clients%20needed%20help%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20use%20the%20screen%20to%20connect%20their%20phone%20to%20the%20car's%20Bluetooth.%20I'd%20walk%20them%20through%20it%20and%20get%20them%20to%20do%20it%20for%20me%20to%20show%20they%20could.%20It%20came%20in%20handy%20that%20I'd%20worked%20in%20the%20library%2C%20where%20I'd%20have%20to%20help%20people%20figure%20out%20the%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20how%20to%20diagnose%20a%20vehicle%2C%20verify%20a%20customer's%20concern%2C%20diagnose%20a%20concern%2C%20fix%20it%2C%20and%20then%20verify%20that%20it's%20fixed.%20I%20was%20called%20out%20to%20help%20a%20few%20celebrity%20clients%2C%20and%20a%20few%20times%2C%20I%20did%20repairs%20on%20cars%20parked%20in%20movie%20studios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20bragged%20to%20my%20family%20that%20I%20was%20the%20most%20glamorous%20mechanic%20in%20the%20world.%20I%20could've%20been%20fixing%20bulldozers%20on%20a%20fracking%20site%20in%20North%20Dakota%2C%20but%20instead%2C%20I%20was%20driving%20around%20LA%20in%20a%20fancy%20race%20car%20and%20changing%20celebrities'%20wiper%20blades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e65dc0c4-62d5-4e16-a0c0-61e7d8572294%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20were%20scared%20of%20Elon%20Musk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20met%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BUncle%20Elon%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20staff%20called%20him.%20Once%2C%20in%202019%2C%20I%20was%20filling%20out%20repair%20forms%20in%20the%20office%20instead%20of%20working%20in%20the%20garage%20because%20I%20had%20a%20vision%20issue%20and%20was%20wearing%20an%20eye%20patch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20technicians%20ran%20into%20the%20room%20and%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BUncle%20Elon%20is%20here.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20drill.%20Clean%20off%20your%20desk%2C%20tuck%20in%20your%20shirt%2C%20whatever%20you%20got%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20worried.%20I'd%20heard%20Elon%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-cofounder-martin-eberhard-on-company-culture-elon-musk-firings-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efire%20people%20on%20the%20spot%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Thankfully%2C%20he%20stayed%20in%20the%20garage%20and%20didn't%20come%20into%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20I%20became%20disillusioned%20with%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20went%20from%20being%20an%20incredible%20place%20to%20work%20to%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-tesla-employees-reveal-the-worst-parts-of-working-there-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterrible%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-part-time-ceo-distracted-by-twitter-spacex-shareholders-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanges%20to%20management%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20on%20vacation%20in%20January%202023.%20When%20I%20came%20back%2C%2